Issues.Body:
Consider the following code:

```
import { Component, OnInit } from "@angular/core";
import { Observable, of, BehaviorSubject } from "rxjs";
import { tap } from "rxjs/operators";

@Component({
  selector: "app-root",
  template: `{{ users$ | async }}
    <div *ngIf="loading$ | async">
          SPINING...
    </div>`,
  styleUrls: [],
})
export class AppComponent implements OnInit {
  users$: Observable<any>;
  loadingSubject = new BehaviorSubject(false);
  loading$ = this.loadingSubject.asObservable();

  constructor() {}

  ngOnInit() {
    this.users$ = of({}).pipe(tap(() => this.loadingSubject.next(true)));
  }
}

```
When you run the code, you get the ExpressionChangedAfterItHasBeenCheckedError in the console. The reason is that the "*ngIf" binding is evaluated first while it's after the "users$" async pipe in the template. 

I expect binding should occur in the same order as in the template.

